WEBVTT

00:17.880 --> 00:25.100
V. And it came to pass, that as the people pressed upon him to hear the word of God,

00:25.100 --> 00:34.580
he stood by the lake of Jenesseret, and saw two ships standing by the lake, but the fishermen were gone out of them and were washing their nets.

00:35.380 --> 00:45.680
And he entered into one of the ships, which was Simon's, and prayed him that he would thrust out a little from the land, and he sat down and taught the people out of the ship.

00:46.360 --> 00:53.680
Now when he had left speaking, he said unto Simon, Launch out into the deep, and let down your nets for a draft.

00:54.920 --> 01:04.140
And Simon answering said unto him, Master, we have toiled all the night, and have taken nothing. Nevertheless, at thy word, I will let down the net.

01:05.280 --> 01:17.060
And when they had done this, they enclosed a great multitude of fishes and their net break, and they beckoned unto their partners, which were in the other ship, that they should come and help them.

01:17.180 --> 01:29.280
And they came and filled both the ships, so that they began to sink. When Simon Peter saw it, he fell down at Jesus's knees, saying, Depart from me, for I am a sinful man, O Lord.

01:29.280 --> 01:35.080
For he was astonished at all that were with him at the draft of the fishes which they had taken.

01:35.880 --> 01:41.320
And so was also James and John, the sons of Zebedee, which were partners with Simon.

01:41.960 --> 01:47.760
And Jesus said unto Simon, Fear not, from henceforth thou shalt catch men.

01:48.520 --> 01:53.060
And when they had brought their ships to land, they forsook all and followed him.

01:53.060 --> 02:06.120
And it came to pass, when he was in a certain city, behold a man full of leprosy, who, seeing Jesus, fell on his face, and besought him, saying, Lord, if thou wilt, thou canst make me clean.

02:06.720 --> 02:15.340
And he put forth his hand, and touched him, saying, I will, be thou clean. And immediately the leprosy departed from him.

02:15.840 --> 02:25.700
And he charged him to tell no man, but go and show thyself to the priest, and offer for thy cleansing, according as Moses commanded, for a testimony unto them.

02:26.380 --> 02:36.520
But so much the more went there of fame abroad of him, and great multitudes came together to hear, and to be healed by him of their infirmities.

02:37.120 --> 02:40.180
And he withdrew himself into the wilderness, and prayed.

02:41.440 --> 02:52.880
And it came to pass, on a certain day, as he was teaching, that there were Pharisees and doctors of the law sitting by, which were come out of every town of Galilee, and Judea, and Jerusalem.

02:52.880 --> 02:56.460
And the power of the Lord was present to heal them.

02:57.640 --> 03:06.000
And behold, men brought in a bed a man which was taken with a palsy, and they sought means to bring him in, and to lay him before him.

03:06.620 --> 03:17.840
And when they could not find by what way they might bring him in because of the multitude, they went upon the housetop, and let him down through the tiling with his couch into the midst before Jesus.

03:17.840 --> 03:24.160
And when he saw their faith, he said unto them, Man, thy sins are forgiven thee.

03:24.820 --> 03:35.060
And the scribes and the Pharisees began to reason, saying, Who is this which speaketh blasphemies? Who can forgive sins but God alone?

03:35.840 --> 03:42.020
But when Jesus perceived their thoughts, he answering said unto them, What reason ye in your hearts?

03:42.020 --> 03:54.280
Whether is easier to say, Thy sins be forgiven thee, or to say, Rise up and walk, but that ye may know that the Son of Man hath power upon earth to forgive sins.

03:55.100 --> 04:03.420
He said unto the sick of the palsy, I say unto thee, Arise, and take up thy couch, and go into thine house.

04:04.060 --> 04:11.160
And immediately he rose up before them, and took up that whereon he lay, and departed to his own house, glorifying God.

04:11.760 --> 04:19.000
And they were all amazed, and they glorified God, and were filled with fear, saying, We have seen strange things today.

04:19.940 --> 04:28.480
And after these things he went forth, and saw a publican named Levi, sitting at the receipt of custom, and he said unto him, Follow me.

04:28.480 --> 04:40.520
And he left all, rose up, and followed him. And Levi made him a great feast in his own house, and there was a great company of publicans and of others that sat down with them.

04:41.100 --> 04:49.040
But their scribes and Pharisees murmured against his disciples, saying, Why do ye eat and drink with publicans and sinners?

04:50.200 --> 04:57.540
And Jesus answering said unto them, They that are whole need not a physician, but they that are sick.

04:57.540 --> 05:02.480
I came not to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.

05:03.360 --> 05:12.520
And they said unto him, Why do the disciples of John fast often, and make prayers, and likewise the disciples of the Pharisees, but thine eat and drink?

05:13.420 --> 05:19.920
And he said unto them, Can ye make the children of the bride chamber fast, while the bridegroom is with them?

05:20.460 --> 05:26.280
But the days will come when the bridegroom shall be taken away from them, and then shall they fast in those days.

05:27.060 --> 05:30.320
And he spake also a parable unto them.

05:31.080 --> 05:41.280
No man putteth a piece of a new garment upon an old. If otherwise, then both the new maketh a rent, and the piece that was taken out of the new agreeeth not with the old.

05:42.000 --> 05:49.620
And no man putteth new wine into old bottles, else the new wine will burst the bottles, and be spilled, and the bottles shall perish.

05:50.220 --> 05:54.280
But new wine must be put into new bottles, and both are preserved.

05:54.280 --> 06:03.080
No man also having drunk old wine, straightway desireth new, for he saith, The old is better.

06:04.300 --> 06:05.420
CHAPTER VI

06:05.420 --> 06:15.560
And it came to pass on the second Sabbath after the first, that he went through the cornfields, and his disciples plucked the ears of corn, and did eat, rubbing them in their hands.

06:16.320 --> 06:22.800
And certain of the Pharisees said unto them, Why do ye that which is not lawful to do on the Sabbath days?

06:23.480 --> 06:33.120
And Jesus answering them said, Have ye not read so much as this what David did when himself was unhungred, and they which were with him?

06:33.440 --> 06:43.040
How he went into the house of God, and did take and eat the shoe-bread, and gave also to them that were with him, which it is not lawful to eat, but for the priests alone.

06:43.800 --> 06:48.800
And he said unto them, That the Son of man is Lord also of the Sabbath.

06:48.800 --> 06:54.560
And it came to pass also on another Sabbath that he entered into the synagogue and taught.

06:55.140 --> 06:57.560
And there was a man whose right hand was withered.

06:58.220 --> 07:06.520
And the scribes and Pharisees watched him, whether he would heal on the Sabbath day, that they might find an accusation against him.

07:06.980 --> 07:14.120
But he knew their thoughts, and said to the man which had the withered hand, Rise up and stand forth in the midst.

07:14.820 --> 07:16.680
And he arose and stood forth.

07:17.920 --> 07:21.980
Then said Jesus unto them, I will ask you one thing.

07:22.380 --> 07:28.400
Is it lawful on the Sabbath days to do good, or to do evil, to save life, or to destroy it?

07:28.920 --> 07:33.940
And looking round about upon them all, he said unto the man, Stretch forth thy hand.

07:34.280 --> 07:38.460
And he did so, and his hand was restored whole as the other.

07:39.140 --> 07:44.660
And they were filled with madness, and communed one with another what they might do to Jesus.

07:44.660 --> 07:51.840
And it came to pass in those days that he went out into a mountain to pray, and continued all night in prayer to God.

07:52.540 --> 07:58.740
And when it was day, he called unto him his disciples, and of them he chose twelve, whom also he named apostles.

08:00.260 --> 08:10.480
Simon, whom he also named Peter, and Andrew his brother, James and John, Philip and Bartholomew, Matthew and Thomas,

08:11.140 --> 08:21.680
James the son of Alphaeus, and Simon called Zalotes, and Judas the brother of James, and Judas Iscariot, which also was the traitor.

08:22.460 --> 08:29.260
And he came down with them, and stood in the plain, and the company of his disciples, and a great multitude of people,

08:29.620 --> 08:38.080
out of all Judea and Jerusalem, and from the sea coast of Tyre and Sidon, which came to hear him, and to be healed of their diseases.

08:38.080 --> 08:42.740
And they that were vexed with unclean spirits, and they were healed.

08:43.580 --> 08:48.580
And the whole multitude sought to touch him, for there went virtue out of him, and healed them all.

08:49.140 --> 08:57.160
And he lifted up his eyes on his disciples, and said, Blessed be ye poor, for yours is the kingdom of God.

08:58.180 --> 09:05.540
Blessed are ye that hunger now, for ye shall be filled. Blessed are ye that weep now, for ye shall laugh.

09:06.320 --> 09:13.420
Blessed are ye when men shall hate you, and when they shall separate you from their company, and shall reproach you,

09:13.720 --> 09:21.420
and cast out your name as evil, for the son of man's sake. Rejoice ye in that day, and leap for joy.

09:21.880 --> 09:28.160
For behold, your reward is great in heaven, for in the like manner did their fathers unto the prophets.

09:28.160 --> 09:37.320
But woe unto you that are rich, for ye have received your consolation. Woe unto you that are full, for ye shall hunger.

09:38.120 --> 09:45.620
Woe unto you that laugh now, for ye shall mourn and weep. Woe unto you when all men shall speak well of you,

09:45.840 --> 09:52.560
for so did their fathers to the false prophets. But I say unto you which hear, Love your enemies,

09:52.560 --> 10:01.140
do good to them which hate you, bless them that curse you, and pray for them which despitefully use you.

10:01.900 --> 10:11.300
And unto him that smiteth thee on the one cheek, offer also the other. And him that taketh away thy cloak, forbid not to take thy coat also.

10:12.640 --> 10:18.500
Give to every man that asketh of thee, and of him that taketh away thy goods, ask them not again.

10:18.500 --> 10:28.000
And as ye would that men should do to you, do ye also to them likewise. For if ye love them which love you, what thank have ye?

10:28.160 --> 10:34.740
For sinners also love those that love them. And if ye do good to them which do good to you, what thank have ye?

10:34.780 --> 10:42.060
For sinners also do even the same. And if ye lend to them of whom ye hope to receive, what thank have ye?

10:42.060 --> 10:50.440
For sinners also lend to sinners to receive as much again. But love ye your enemies, and do good, and lend.

10:50.940 --> 11:00.400
Hoping for nothing again, and your reward shall be great. And ye shall be the children of the highest, for he is kind unto the unthankful and to the evil.

11:01.340 --> 11:09.260
Be ye therefore merciful, as your Father also is merciful. Judge not, and ye shall not be judged.

11:09.980 --> 11:16.340
Condemn not, and ye shall not be condemned. Forgive, and ye shall be forgiven.

11:17.300 --> 11:25.980
Give, and it shall be given unto you, good measure, pressed down, and shaken together, and running over, shall men give into your bosom.

11:25.980 --> 11:31.380
For with the same measure that ye meet withal, it shall be measured to you again.

11:32.360 --> 11:39.760
And he spake a parable unto them. Can the blind lead the blind? Shall they not both fall into the ditch?

11:40.500 --> 11:46.500
The disciple is not above his master, but every one that is perfect shall be as his master.

11:46.500 --> 11:55.720
And why beholdest thou the mote that is in thy brother's eye, but perceivest not the beam that is in thine own eye?

11:57.200 --> 12:09.220
Either how canst thou say to thy brother, Brother, let me pull out the mote that is in thine eye, when thou thyself beholdest not the beam that is in thine own eye.

12:09.220 --> 12:19.760
Thou hypocrite, cast out first the beam out of thine own eye, and then shalt thou see clearly to pull out the mote that is in thy brother's eye.

12:20.520 --> 12:27.180
For a good tree bringeth not forth corrupt fruit, neither doth a corrupt tree bring forth good fruit.

12:27.840 --> 12:36.260
For every tree is known by his own fruit. For of thorns men do not gather figs, nor of a bramble bush gather they grapes.

12:37.100 --> 12:47.400
A good man out of the good treasure of his heart bringeth forth that which is good, and an evil man out of the evil treasure of his heart bringeth forth that which is evil.

12:48.300 --> 12:51.740
For of the abundance of the heart his mouth speaketh.

12:52.500 --> 13:05.080
And why call ye me, Lord, Lord, and do not the things which I say? Whosoever cometh to me, and heareth my sayings, and doeth them, I will show you to whom he is like.

13:05.080 --> 13:20.560
He is like a man which built an house and digged deep and laid the foundation on a rock, and when the flood arose the stream beat vehemently upon that house and could not shake it, for it was founded upon a rock.

13:20.560 --> 13:37.360
But he that heareth and doeth not is like a man that without a foundation built an house upon the earth, against which the stream did beat vehemently, and immediately it fell, and the ruin of that house was great.

